<TEXT>
after two months of legal arguments that 
held up six death sentences florida proved its electric chair 
works by executing a killer who said he felt no guilt for robbing 
raping and stabbing a woman 
anthony bertolotti 38 died friday evening in the first 
electrocution carried out by the state since may 4 when flame and 
smoke shot from the headpiece of the electric chair during the 
execution of jesse tafero 
state and federal courts stayed the executions of bertolotti and 
five other death row inmates while considering arguments from 
defense lawyers that the 66yearold chair would torture their 
clients to death 
an orlando trial court conducted tests on the chair and ruled 
wednesday it was fit for use the 11th circuit court of appeal and 
the us supreme court concurred and the execution went forward 
friday evening 
bertolotti jerked back in the chair clenched his fists and 
slumped after each of the three surges administered by the hooded 
executioner 
there were white whisps of smoke as is usual for the 
electrocutions but no signs of malfunction bertolotti was 
declared dead at 707 pm 
the execution was floridas 23rd since it resumed capital 
punishment in 1979 and the 136th in the nation since the supreme 
court reinstated the death penalty in 1976 
the state had concluded that an artificial sponge used in 
place of a natural sponge under the electrode in the headpiece 
burst into flame during the tafero electrocution gov bob martinez 
said the sponge had been replaced and the chair worked properly 
bertolottis lawyers lost their argument that the chair was 
faulty in a hearing wednesday before us district judge g kendall 
sharp in orlando 
a threejudge panel rejected the condemned mans claim that 
sharps ruling was unfounded and the us supreme court rejected 
the case after taking it up about half an hour before the sentence 
was carried out 
it is gratifying that the courts concluded floridas electric 
chair does in fact work as it is designed to that fact was borne 
out by extensive testing earlier this week and the completion of 
this execution proves it conclusively martinez said 
the 11th circuit court of appeal held up three other death 
warrants and state courts held up two others while the chairs 
function was tested other matters of appeal stood in the way of 
some of those death sentences 
bertolotti was sentenced to die for the sept 27 1983 murder 
of carol ward 48 of orlando she was working in her yard when 
bertolotti approached and asked to use the telephone and she let 
him in 
he grabbed a knife and robbed her of 30 then stabbed her 
repeatedly until the knife broke he found another knife and 
stabbed her until she died leaving the knife in her body at some 
point bertolotti removed her clothes and raped her he was 
convicted march 31 1984 
bertolotti wrote several letters to prosecutors after his 
conviction saying he wasnt sorry 
i have no regrets or sorrows for the murder of carol ward 
he wrote she should have locked her damn door i really did a 
favor by taking her life dont you think so 
</TEXT>
