<TEXT>
singersongwriter john hiatt says hes not 
so choosy anymore about how he does his composing 
i used to need the right pencils the right paper the right 
room and no one around now it doesnt matter said hiatt whose 
more than 600 songs include thing called loved a hit for 
bonnie raitt and slow turning 
ive learned to be able to write without all the planets being 
in perfect harmony he said in an interview to promote a concert 
appearance next wednesday i can write on an airplane in the 
back of the bus in the laundry room with the television blasting 
whatever the circumstances 
in the past hiatt said many of his songs reflected the fact 
