senate democrats on friday joined republicans in calling for a 
total abolition of the special interest political action committees 
responsible for raising 45 million of the 180 million spent on 
senate campaigns in the 1988 elections 
with the senate scheduled to vote next week on campaign finance 
reform legislation the move by democratic leaders effectively 
denied republicans a chance to force a vote on pacs and portray 
