it wasnt long after theodore roosevelt named 
oliver wendell holmes to the supreme court that he wished he hadnt 
holmes cast an important vote against roosevelts trustbusting 
efforts 
i could carve out of a banana a judge with more backbone 
sputtered roosevelt 
maybe it is an omen that david h souter the appeals court 
judge from new hampshire selected last week by president bush for 
the supreme court is said to emulate the values and philosophy of 
holmes 
at harvard his senior thesis was on holmes judicial 
philosophy souter still follows a course of reading laid out by 
his fellow new englander 
over the years supreme court justices have shown an independent 
streak unforeseen by their presidential appointers 
the truth is that presidents can nominate justices but cant 
dominate them once on the bench jurists sometimes cause dismay 
for their sponsors 
dwight eisenhower regretted that hed named two justices who 
became liberal activists earl warren and william j brennan after 
leaving office ike was asked if he had made any substantial 
mistakes yes he is supposed to have said two and they are 
both sitting on the supreme court 
how was he to know when he appointed warren that his chief 
justice would lead the court into overthrowing segregation in 
public schools an earthquake of a decision and one that 
eisenhower never gave any sign of being happy about 
nor could ike have foreseen brennans forceful liberal impact 
brennan had been an obscure member of the new jersey supreme court 
eisenhower picked him because his first choice the chief justice 
of that court was too ill and recommended brennan instead 
nobody knows how a judge is likely to turn out until the judge 
actually sits on a bench said bernard schwartz a law professor 
at new york university and author of a new book about the warren 
burger court the ascent of pragmatism 
his best example of a justice who surprised his sponsor is felix 
frankfurter 
frankfurter he said was so radical he was almost considered 
a red when franklin d roosevelt appointed him 
once in robes frankfurter became a leader of the judicial 
restraint camp one of the nations leading civil libertarian 
lawyers turned into a thorn to libertarian causes 
of the eight justices on todays supreme court four byron 
white harry blackmun john paul stevens and sandra day oconnor 
