nation until after the dec 2 elections 
the outcome of the dispute will determine the leadership of a 
united germany by deciding how many votes each party needs for 
parliamentary representation to win seats parties will need to 
win more votes in an election for a unified nation than in separate 
east and west german balloting 
west german law requires a minimum 5 percent showing for 
parliamentary representation and the two sides are now trying to 
agree on whether the same minimum should apply in elections planned 
dec 2 that will unify the germanys 
one proposal would involve votecounting separately in each of 
the 16 states of a unified germany another suggestion put forward 
saturday would allow smaller parties to appear on the same ballot 
as larger ones thereby increasing their chances for representation 
that practice is allowed in east german elections but not for 
national elections in west germany 
