university suggested another possible reason for the legislatures 
affection for issues of morality the states sorry financial 
condition 
until a few years ago parent said balancing the states 
multibilliondollar budget was easy oil prices were high and oil 
taxes paid for everything 
things changed when oil prices plummeted in the mid1980s 
lawmakers have had to cut services put supposedly temporary 
sales taxes on traditionally exempt items such as groceries and 
medicine and fight over roemers tax overhaul proposals most of 
which have died 
issues of abortion the flag and smutty or drugrelated records 
were easy to deal with when the alternatives were a tight budget 
and unpopular taxes parent said 
these were almost welcome distractions said parent 
former state rep kevin reilly who once called louisiana a 
banana republic agreed with that assessment 
its a diversionary tactic no question about it said 
reilly who left the house in 1987 to devote more time to business 
and every legislative body does that he added the united 
