parliament arguing the current chamber is tainted by the 1989 
political deal that set aside a portion of seats for communists 
walesa strategists believe they can put together enough votes in 
parliament to elect the solidarity chairman president where he 
would oversee the drafting of an entirely new postcommunist 
constitution the new party sees walesa as politically vulnerable 
in a direct election 
the new partys membership includes most of walesas longtime 
advisers and allies in solidarity including filmmaker andrzej 
wajda parliamentary secretary henryk wujec and government 
ministers aleksander hall jacek kuron and witold trzeciakowski 
president wojciech jaruzelski the former communist party 
leader elected to a sixyear term a year ago already has signaled 
he will step down early 
he sent a letter to parliament on saturday saying he agreed with 
a planned september discussion on holding early presidential and 
parliamentary elections 
jaruzelskis election was meant to prevent the soviets from 
stepping in to quash reforms but now that soviet influence has 
