forsythe said 
the second case could affect millions of working women the 
court must decide whether employers may exclude all women of 
childbearing age from some hazardous but comparatively 
highpaying jobs to protect their fetuses 
at issue is a car battery manufacturers policy of banning women 
who cannot prove they are infertile from jobs that expose them to 
lead 
