rebel soldiers fought to within one 
mile of president samuel does fortified mansion on saturday and 
battled pockets of government troops for control of a hill 
overlooking the city center 
meanwhile five european ambassadors warned that the country was 
slipping into anarchy and national suicide called for an 
urgent un security council meeting and suggested that us 
troops intervene 
while the forces of national patriotic front leader charles 
taylor remained blocked by government troops six miles east of the 
capital the smaller force of a rival rebel leader prince johnson 
advanced into the city 
johnsons disciplined rebel forces neatly dressed in camouflage 
uniforms carefully picked off snipers nests as they moved up the 
steep hill toward the ducor palace hotel which has a view of the 
city center rifle and machine gun fire reverberated across the 
hill as civilians hid in their houses 
johnsons rebels took control of the waterside and west point 
districts at the city end of one of the two bridges from bushrod 
island the island is on the opposite side of the city from does 
mansion one mile away 
doe has pledged to make his final stand inside the heavily 
fortified mansion the rebels who began their offensive in 
december accuse the government of corruption and human rights 
abuses and demand does resignation 
the five ambassadors representing european economic community 
nations issued their warning friday italian ambassador gianguido 
lanzoni advised his government on behalf of all the eec ambassadors 
that the interdependence of nations no longer permits other 
nations to sit idle while one country plunges into anarchy and 
national suicide 
there is no longer any effective government in control of this 
country lanzoni told his government in a cable he advised his 
government to call the un security council into emergency session 
to discuss the chaos and killing of civilians on both sides in 
liberias civil war 
and he suggested the european countries should look favorably on 
any american move to intervene in view of the special 
relationship between liberia and the united states there are 
four us warships off the coast of the west african nation 
founded by the descendants of freed american slaves 
but the united states has refused to intervene saying the war 
is an internal liberian affair 
the civil war has degenerated into tribal war between members of 
does krahn tribe and gio and mano tribesmen many of whom support 
the rebels diplomats say both sides have indiscriminately killed 
civilians 
