taxes in a letter to the administration before the meeting 
the bipartisan national governors association has a 
longstanding policy against such a move spokeswoman rae bond said 
the governors argue that limiting or eliminating deductibility 
in addition to raising federal taxes for individuals who itemize 
their deductions would make it more difficult for states to raise 
additional revenues to provide new services and might lead to 
increased pressure to lower state and local taxes 
the governors also dislike any proposals to raise federal excise 
taxes viewing that as an infringement on state and local tax bases 
the governors are very apprehensive about anything that would 
reduce the flexibility of states to be able to deal with their own 
situation in terms of revenue sources that are traditionally the 
states branstad said 
