income tax to become a tax on a tax and would especially hit 
northeastern states where 18 percent of the national population 
pays 30 percent of all state and local personal and property taxes 
it would strike especially hard at middle and workingclass 
families they said as a region the northeast is already 
suffering from the disproportionate impact of the savings and loan 
bailout 
the tax idea emerged late last week from negotiations on a 
federal budget solution under the gop plan the currently 
unlimited deduction for state and local taxes would be limited to 
10000 administration officials estimated the plan would generate 
3 billion a year in federal revenue 
in addition federal budget negotiators are discussing raising 
the federal excise tax on beer and other alcoholic beverages 
generating 72 billion 
several democratic governors were considering offering proposals 
on the savingsandloan costs including richard celeste of ohio 
michael dukakis of massachusetts and douglas wilder of virginia 
one plan circulated by wilder would call for a national 
commission to investigate the collapse of savings and loans that 
threaten to cost federal taxpayers as much as 300 billion or more 
in bailout costs 
on education a disagreement emerged over the makeup of a 
commission that would issue report cards on how states are doing in 
meeting their education goals an administration plan to have four 
seats each named by the administration the governors and congress 
would leave it dominated 8 to 4 by republicans and was being 
opposed by democrats who feared it could become a partisan weapon 
that has been a very sensitive area branstad acknowledged 
clinton said house speaker tom foley and senate majority leader 
george mitchell have written the governors suggesting the 
commission be established by an act of congress clinton said the 
governors hadnt decided on a response id say well all get a 
bad grade or somebody will get a bad grade if this report card 
