individuals claim a deduction of over 10000 for state and local 
income taxes however on returns filed in 1989 the 46 percent of 
taxpayers who itemized deductions claimed a writeoff averaging only 
about 3800 for income and property taxes combined the proposal 
would not affect the deduction of property taxes 
