<DOCNO> AP900728-0124 </DOCNO>
<TEXT>
heres a brief look at pertinent 
facts about mongolia 
geography mongolia is a landlocked country of about 600000 
square miles of rolling grassland and mountains its highest point 
is in the altai mountains in the west which rise 14420 feet 
average rainfall is only eight inches a year with the gobi desert 
in the south getting as little as 24 inches 
people mongolias population was estimated at 2 million in 
1988 most are ethnic mongols but a tiny minority are khazak 
russian and other minorities one quarter of mongolians live in the 
capital city ulan bator and half live in rural areas mostly 
engaged in herding few true nomads remain but many people are 
seminomadic moving with their herds between winter and summer 
camps 
history genghis khan united the scattered nomadic mongol 
tribes in the 13th century and turned them into a conquering horde 
at its peak the mongol empire he founded claimed territory from 
the danube river in europe to chinas pacific coast the manchus 
ousted the mongols as rulers of china in 1691 the mongols ruled 
mongolia until 1921 a small band of revolutionaries aided by 
soviet troops revolted that year and proclaimed an independent 
socialist state in northern or outer mongolia the southern party 
inner mongolia remained part of china mongolia remained in the 
soviet bloc and began its recent moves toward political and 
economic reform only after moscow did 
economy the economy centers around herding and developing 
natural resources such as copper molybdenum and timber with 25 
million head of livestock mongolia exports wool leather and meat 
less than 1 percent of the land is cultivated the economy is 
centrally planned and major industries are statesubsidized 
mongolia receives substantial aid and investment from the soviet 
union but in april 1990 approved a joint venture law intended to 
encourage investment from japan and the west 
government after nearly seven decades of monopoly the 
communists bowed to popular demonstrations earlier this year and 
legalized other parties however the communist party formally 
called the mongolian peoples revolutionary party has 98000 
members and far outnumbers the opposition the secondlargest party 
is the mongolian democratic party with a declared membership of 
7200 the communists have promised to stop receiving state funds 
but retain cells in the army and police force 
</TEXT>
</DOC>

