<TEXT>
a half dozen us corporations ranging from a 
leading cosmetics maker to the parent publisher of usa today are 
among the best companies for working women according to a business 
magazine 
business week magazines cover story in aug 6 editions released 
friday said avon products cbs dayton hudson gannett kelly 
services and us west communications were leaders in corporate 
efforts to promote what the magazine called womanfriendly 
cultures 
the magazine also listed 12 companies in the nextbest category 
of upand comers american express baxter international 
corning honeywell ibm johnson amp johnson merck monsanto pitney 
bowes readers digest security pacific bank and square d 
it also listed an additional six in the no 3 category of late 
bloomers digital equipment du pont hewlettpackard olin 3m 
and xerox 
business week said it based the selections on several criteria 
including the numbers of women in key executive positions and on 
the boards of directors efforts to help women advance and 
sensitivity to family issues such as child care and parental leave 
the magazine is not the first publication to produce a 
bestcompanies list for women working woman and working mother 
magazines also have done their own rankings in recent years 
in 1988 two researchers baila zeitz and lorraine dusky 
produced a widely quoted book called the best companies for 
women a compilation of 50 companies with details on their 
recruitment promotion opportunities salary commitment to 
equality flexibility toward parental obligations and policies on 
sexual harassment 
